-- South Africa’s Sterne Wins Golf’s Joburg Open by Seven Shots
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-02-10T12:48:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-10/south-africa-s-sterne-wins-golf-s-joburg-open-by-seven-shots.html
South Africa’s  Richard Sterne  scored
a final-round 64, 8-under par to win golf’s Joburg Open in a
tournament-record score.  Sterne finished on 27-under in Johannesburg, seven shots
ahead of compatriot  Charl Schwartzel  in second. It was Sterne’s
first European Tour win since 2009.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 